The '''Pharmacy Practice Research Trust''' (PPRT) was an independent [[Charitable organization|charity]] established in July 1999, by the [http://www.rpharms.com Royal Pharmaceutical Society]. It aims were support and promote the professional practice and development of [[pharmacist]]s and develop the field of [[Pharmacy Practice Research]]. In January 2013 the PPRT was [http://www.charity-commission.gov.uk/Showcharity/RegisterOfCharities/RemovedCharityMain.aspx?RegisteredCharityNumber=1076457&SubsidiaryNumber=0 wound up] and a new charity [http://www.pharmacyresearchuk.org/ Pharmacy Research UK] was launched in its place.

